Business Brief -- Buffton Corp.:
   Company Will Post Loss
   For Quarter and 6 Months
Buffton also said it has obtained a commitment from
Congress Financial Corp. to pay off and refinance the Bank of
Boston loan after the sale of the subsidiary. The Bank of
Boston loan matures April 1.
   Buffton said the buyer of the subsidiary, BD Instruments
 Avionics Inc., is "a substantial publicly held corporation
headquartered in the United Kingdom."
   For the second quarter ended last March, the manufacturing
concern posted earnings of $285,000, or seven cents a share,
on revenue of $16.7 million.